cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a new approach for training deep neural networks to solve visual recognition tasks, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new learning approach for training DNNs. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper focuses on visual recognition tasks. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories as the paper deals with deep neural networks. Finally, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with natural language processing, but it could be relevant if the visual recognition tasks involve text recognition.
